    "summary": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "A decision is made according to what might be pleasing to imagine, rather than according to evidence or reason.",
        "spans": []
      }
    ],
    "description": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Psychologically, \"wishful thinking\" is believing something because of a desire—\"wish\"—that it be true. As a logical fallacy, Wishful Thinking is an argument whose premise expresses a desire for the conclusion to be true.",
